cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.MA, cs.SOC, cs.LG 

This paper deals with the problem of identifying influential users in a social network for the purpose of advertising multiple products while considering budget and time constraints. This problem falls under the category of social network analysis and optimization, which is covered by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also proposes a submodular maximization algorithm, which involves optimization and combinatorial optimization, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) likely categories as well. The paper also deals with the diffusion of information in a network, which is a topic covered by cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks). Finally, the paper uses mathematical formulations and analysis to prove the efficiency of the proposed algorithm, which falls under the category of machine learning and optimization, covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning).
